				<h1>Holiday Clubs</h1>
				
				<p>Every year in August we hold a Summer Holiday Club for <strong>children of ages 5-11</strong>.</p><br />
				
				<p><strong>The dates for next year's club will appear here soon, with details coming later.</strong></p><br />
				
				<p>The club sessions take place from <strong>10am to 12 noon each day</strong> with a <strong>Grand Finale on the Friday beginning at 6pm</strong> to which families are invited. The whole club is <strong>free of charge</strong>, apart from tickets for food on the Friday evening which will be sold during the week of the club.</p>
				
				<p>Each year we have <strong>songs, games, quizzes, crafts, and more</strong>, so there's something for everyone.</p>

				<h1>Summer Holiday Club 2013</h1><br />
				
				<img src="images/hc_2013_logo.jpg" alt="Holiday Club 2013 Story Keepers" id="hclogo" width="610" height="344" /><br /><br />
				
				<div id="hcparagraphs">
				
				<p>This year's summer Holiday Club, <strong>Story Keepers</strong>, was held from Tuesday 13th August to Friday 16th August.</p>

				<p><strong>"Story Keepers" was originally an animated children's TV series</strong> and re-tells events in the life of Jesus through the eyes of children living shortly afterwards, who have lots of fun and adventure at the expense of the Roman authorities!</p>
				
				<p>We had a great team once again this year, with combined efforts from both this church and St. Andrew's. The club went amazingly smoothly and we had one of the highest attendances that we've had in years. The children and everyone on the team had a great time.</p>
				</div>

				<p>-----------------</p>
				
				<p>If you have any queries about our holiday clubs, then please don't hesitate to <a href="mailto:paul@ferringbaptist.org.uk">contact us</a>!</p>
				
				<p>-----------------</p>
				
